{"article_id":"Tvt6LsrKSXbaldmO","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"What Kind Of 'Jobs President ' Has Obama Been","depth":2},{"id":1,"text":"- In 8 Charts","depth":2},{"id":2,"text":"The final chapter of the Obama economy drew that much closer to its end on Friday , with the final jobs report of the 44th president 's time in office .","depth":6},{"id":3,"text":"That report showed the 75th straight month of job growth ,","depth":7},{"id":4,"text":"with employers adding 156,000 jobs .","depth":7},{"id":5,"text":"In that way , it was emblematic of how the job market has generally fared since the worst of the Great Recession 's aftermath :","depth":6},{"id":6,"text":"chugging along ,","depth":7},{"id":7,"text":"slowly but surely recovering .","depth":7},{"id":8,"text":"With the final Obama administration jobs day in the books , it 's a good time","depth":6},{"id":9,"text":"to look at how American workers have fared .","depth":6},{"id":10,"text":"Donald Trump will inherit a job market","depth":8},{"id":11,"text":"that is vastly rehabilitated from devastating lows just a few years ago .","depth":8},{"id":12,"text":"However , it has also undergone profound changes","depth":8},{"id":13,"text":"that have scarred many American workers .","depth":8},{"id":14,"text":"As Obama prepares to leave office ,","depth":9},{"id":15,"text":"the unemployment rate is at 4.7 percent , less than half of the peak","depth":10},{"id":16,"text":"it reached in October 2009 .","depth":10},{"id":17,"text":"That decline is the result of a prolonged period of job growth .","depth":8},{"id":18,"text":"The administration has grown fond of showing off its prolonged run of job growth every month .","depth":9},{"id":19,"text":"Fastest wage growth since the start of the recovery","depth":10},{"id":20,"text":"✓https : //t.co/uo6Mz0WggU","depth":11},{"id":21,"text":"# JobsReport pic.twitter.com/DUjA4cmPWg","depth":11},{"id":22,"text":"- The White House","depth":10},{"id":23,"text":"( @ WhiteHouse )","depth":10},{"id":24,"text":"January 6 , 2017","depth":9},{"id":25,"text":"For some perspective , here 's how big that job growth was :","depth":6},{"id":26,"text":"Obama averaged 109,000 jobs per month .","depth":8},{"id":27,"text":"That 's far better","depth":11},{"id":28,"text":"than either President Bush experienced ,","depth":11},{"id":29,"text":"but it 's well below the 242,000","depth":11},{"id":30,"text":"that Bill Clinton presided over in the roaring 1990s .","depth":11},{"id":31,"text":"For Reagan , it was 166,000 .","depth":9},{"id":32,"text":"Of course , President Obama came into office","depth":9},{"id":33,"text":"as the economy was plunging into a recession","depth":10},{"id":34,"text":"( a plunge","depth":11},{"id":35,"text":"that also drags down George W. Bush 's number ) .","depth":11},{"id":36,"text":"But","depth":9},{"id":37,"text":"even","depth":10},{"id":38,"text":"if you average out Obama 's 75 straight months of job growth ,","depth":11},{"id":39,"text":"you get 199,000 jobs per month , still shy of Clinton 's economy .","depth":11},{"id":40,"text":"In other words , the Obama recovery has been moderate , but remarkably steady .","depth":6},{"id":41,"text":"The question is how long that steady climb can continue uninterrupted .","depth":6},{"id":42,"text":"The unemployment rate is already near a nine-year low ,","depth":6},{"id":43,"text":"as Steven Russolillo at the Wall Street Journal pointed out this week ,","depth":6},{"id":44,"text":"and there is some question among economists","depth":6},{"id":45,"text":"how low it can go .","depth":6},{"id":46,"text":"Having a job is one thing .","depth":5},{"id":47,"text":"Having a job","depth":7},{"id":48,"text":"that pays well","depth":7},{"id":49,"text":"is another .","depth":6},{"id":50,"text":"And slowly through Obama 's tenure , those wages have inched upward .","depth":6},{"id":51,"text":"In fact , wages were one bright spot of Friday 's jobs report .","depth":8},{"id":52,"text":"Average hourly wages were up by 2.9 percent in December .","depth":10},{"id":53,"text":"After several years of hovering around 2 percent ,","depth":10},{"id":54,"text":"that 's welcome growth .","depth":9},{"id":55,"text":"Aside from meaning more money in workers ' pockets ,","depth":8},{"id":56,"text":"wage growth serves as yet another sign of a tightening labor market ,","depth":9},{"id":57,"text":"signaling","depth":10},{"id":58,"text":"that employers are willing to pay more","depth":11},{"id":59,"text":"to attract workers .","depth":11},{"id":60,"text":"Rising wages may inspire the Federal Reserve to take its foot further off the gas pedal in the coming months","depth":8},{"id":61,"text":"( that is , allow interest rates to rise ) -","depth":8},{"id":62,"text":"a reminder","depth":8},{"id":63,"text":"that the economy is n't exactly under the president 's control .","depth":8},{"id":64,"text":"( More on this later . )","depth":6},{"id":65,"text":"Labor force participation is low ,","depth":6},{"id":66,"text":"but what does it mean ?","depth":6},{"id":67,"text":"This one became a flashpoint in the presidential election ,","depth":10},{"id":68,"text":"with Trump at times pointing out","depth":11},{"id":69,"text":"how much the labor force shrank under Obama .","depth":11},{"id":70,"text":"The main measure of this is the labor force participation rate","depth":12},{"id":71,"text":"- that is , the percentage of people","depth":13},{"id":72,"text":"who are either working or looking for work","depth":14},{"id":73,"text":"( that is , who are in the labor force ) .","depth":14},{"id":74,"text":"That figure was at 65.7 percent in January 2009 , at the start of Obama 's presidency ,","depth":13},{"id":75,"text":"and today is at 62.7 percent","depth":14},{"id":76,"text":"- a steep drop .","depth":14},{"id":77,"text":"And today , the figure is well below its 2000 high of 67.3 percent .","depth":12},{"id":78,"text":"But it 's not clear how bad or how benign that change is .","depth":10},{"id":79,"text":"Many Americans are out of the labor force","depth":11},{"id":80,"text":"and entirely happy about it .","depth":11},{"id":81,"text":"Quitting work","depth":12},{"id":82,"text":"to retire ,","depth":12},{"id":83,"text":"for example , is a totally nonalarming reason","depth":12},{"id":84,"text":"to leave the labor force .","depth":12},{"id":85,"text":"But then , there may be many people","depth":12},{"id":86,"text":"who ,","depth":13},{"id":87,"text":"facing a tough job market ,","depth":14},{"id":88,"text":"have given up looking for work .","depth":14},{"id":89,"text":"That 's not good ,","depth":11},{"id":90,"text":"and it also happened for many Americans both during and after the recession .","depth":10},{"id":91,"text":"In the aftermath of the recession , economists have tried to figure out exactly how many people are voluntarily versus involuntarily out of the labor force .","depth":8},{"id":92,"text":"As of 2014 , the nonpartisan Congressional Budget Office estimated","depth":11},{"id":93,"text":"that half the decline in the participation rate at that time had come from `` long-term trends '' like aging","depth":12},{"id":94,"text":"- as baby boomers age ,","depth":13},{"id":95,"text":"that means a large chunk of the population will naturally retire .","depth":13},{"id":96,"text":"But that left half of the decline a result of economic weakness and a slow recovery , in the CBO 's estimation .","depth":10},{"id":97,"text":"Should the participation rate hold steady or creep upward during a Trump presidency ,","depth":12},{"id":98,"text":"that could keep the unemployment rate from dropping ,","depth":12},{"id":99,"text":"as only Americans","depth":13},{"id":100,"text":"who are looking for work","depth":13},{"id":101,"text":"are counted as `` unemployed . ''","depth":12},{"id":102,"text":"That would be one of those cases","depth":11},{"id":103,"text":"where a slightly higher unemployment rate could be a good thing .","depth":11},{"id":104,"text":"Full-time job growth over the course of the Obama presidency has far outstripped part-time job growth ,","depth":10},{"id":105,"text":"as FiveThirtyEight 's Ben Casselman has pointed out .","depth":10},{"id":106,"text":"Part-time jobs ticked up in November ,","depth":10},{"id":107,"text":"but overall , employment growth in recovery has been almost all full-time .","depth":10},{"id":108,"text":"pic.twitter.com/m1MrB1ZA3e","depth":9},{"id":109,"text":"- Ben Casselman","depth":11},{"id":110,"text":"( @ bencasselman )","depth":11},{"id":111,"text":"December 2 , 2016","depth":10},{"id":112,"text":"Of course , some of those people","depth":11},{"id":113,"text":"working part time","depth":11},{"id":114,"text":"want to be working part time ,","depth":10},{"id":115,"text":"and some do n't .","depth":9},{"id":116,"text":"Another bright spot here is that the share of those workers","depth":12},{"id":117,"text":"who are involuntarily part time","depth":12},{"id":118,"text":"has fallen off .","depth":11},{"id":119,"text":"However , that figure is still a fair bit higher","depth":12},{"id":120,"text":"than it was prior to the recession","depth":12},{"id":121,"text":"( and that level was itself , in turn , higher","depth":12},{"id":122,"text":"than it was before the prior recession ) .","depth":12},{"id":123,"text":"That 's one place","depth":11},{"id":124,"text":"where there could still be some improvement","depth":11},{"id":125,"text":"- there are still about 1 million more of those involuntary part-time workers","depth":11},{"id":126,"text":"than there were prior to the recession .","depth":11},{"id":127,"text":"Politicians of both parties love to talk about manufacturing .","depth":11},{"id":128,"text":"Obama pushed manufacturing initiatives throughout his presidency ,","depth":12},{"id":129,"text":"and Trump built much of his economic message during the campaign","depth":13},{"id":130,"text":"around singing the praises of America 's manufacturers .","depth":13},{"id":131,"text":"But","depth":11},{"id":132,"text":"when it comes to employment ,","depth":12},{"id":133,"text":"the goods-producing share of the economy has continued to fall .","depth":12},{"id":134,"text":"Throughout the past few decades , the share of Americans","depth":12},{"id":135,"text":"who make things","depth":13},{"id":136,"text":"- people in manufacturing , mining , logging and construction -","depth":13},{"id":137,"text":"has fallen off ,","depth":11},{"id":138,"text":"and that trend continued during the recent recession ,","depth":11},{"id":139,"text":"finally flattening out toward the end .","depth":11},{"id":140,"text":"We present this chart over a longer time frame ,","depth":12},{"id":141,"text":"which makes it a little bit of a cheat","depth":12},{"id":142,"text":"- this is n't exactly a measure of Obama 's `` record on jobs . ''","depth":11},{"id":143,"text":"Nor is it necessarily a measure of economic weakness ;","depth":11},{"id":144,"text":"in fact , manufacturing has , thanks to technological advances , maintained strong output","depth":12},{"id":145,"text":"while shedding workers .","depth":12},{"id":146,"text":"It 's a reminder","depth":10},{"id":147,"text":"that all the usual macroeconomic indicators","depth":13},{"id":148,"text":"( unemployment , wages , labor force participation , GDP )","depth":13},{"id":149,"text":"can quantify a lot of things in the economy ,","depth":12},{"id":150,"text":"but you have to dig in","depth":12},{"id":151,"text":"to learn about the quality of that economy","depth":13},{"id":152,"text":"- what exactly is going on behind those numbers .","depth":13},{"id":153,"text":"This decline in goods-producing jobs does n't signal","depth":9},{"id":154,"text":"that the economy is getting worse or better -","depth":9},{"id":155,"text":"it 's just changing ,","depth":9},{"id":156,"text":"in this case to become more focused on providing services , instead of goods .","depth":9},{"id":157,"text":"All of this is to say","depth":9},{"id":158,"text":"that Trump inherits a job market","depth":11},{"id":159,"text":"that is humming along comfortably ,","depth":11},{"id":160,"text":"given how poor of shape it was in only recently .","depth":10},{"id":161,"text":"But it 's also an economy","depth":11},{"id":162,"text":"that has sharply moved away from manufacturing and other goods-producing industries","depth":12},{"id":163,"text":"- the very ones","depth":13},{"id":164,"text":"he pushed the most in the election .","depth":13},{"id":165,"text":"That change has hurt plenty of Americans ,","depth":11},{"id":166,"text":"despite the job market 's improvement .","depth":11},{"id":167,"text":"Trump has tried to claim credit for several hundred goods-producing jobs here and there","depth":12},{"id":168,"text":"( credit","depth":14},{"id":169,"text":"that he does n't always deserve ,","depth":14},{"id":170,"text":"as the Washington Post 's Philip Bump has reported ) ,","depth":13},{"id":171,"text":"but bringing manufacturing employment back in a sizable way seems like a tall order for any president .","depth":11},{"id":172,"text":"Furthermore , alternative work","depth":12},{"id":173,"text":"- like driving an Uber or Lyft -","depth":12},{"id":174,"text":"continues to grow quickly as a share of the economy .","depth":11},{"id":175,"text":"That change could eventually require policy attention ,","depth":8},{"id":176,"text":"as more workers take jobs","depth":9},{"id":177,"text":"that do n't come with benefits .","depth":9},{"id":178,"text":"But there 's another big caveat here .","depth":7},{"id":179,"text":"Presidents get lots of credit and blame for the economy 's performance ,","depth":9},{"id":180,"text":"despite the fact","depth":10},{"id":181,"text":"that they do n't really have firm control over that performance .","depth":10},{"id":182,"text":"( If they did ,","depth":9},{"id":183,"text":"why would recessions ever happen ? )","depth":9},{"id":184,"text":"Yes , a president can push an economic agenda","depth":8},{"id":185,"text":"and in some cases push particular policies","depth":10},{"id":186,"text":"that end up having a sizable impact on the economy","depth":10},{"id":187,"text":"( see : the 2009 stimulus package ,","depth":10},{"id":188,"text":"which undeniably had a positive impact ) .","depth":10},{"id":189,"text":"But they also need Congress","depth":9},{"id":190,"text":"to enact those policies .","depth":9},{"id":191,"text":"Not only that , but the Federal Reserve has its own set of controls -","depth":10},{"id":192,"text":"a set","depth":11},{"id":193,"text":"to which the president does not have access ,","depth":12},{"id":194,"text":"despite some conspiracies of politically motivated Fed scale-tipping .","depth":12},{"id":195,"text":"So , like Obama , whatever happens to the economy under Trump , he may not deserve whatever credit","depth":11},{"id":196,"text":"he may claim","depth":11},{"id":197,"text":"( and the same goes for whatever blame is thrown his way ) .","depth":10}],"relations":[{"parent":395,"left":199,"right":394,"relation":"organization","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":199,"left":0,"right":1,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":394,"left":242,"right":393,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":242,"left":221,"right":241,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":221,"left":204,"right":220,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":204,"left":201,"right":203,"relation":"evaluation","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":201,"left":2,"right":200,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":200,"left":3,"right":4,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":203,"left":5,"right":202,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":202,"left":6,"right":7,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":220,"left":205,"right":219,"relation":"organization","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":205,"left":8,"right":9,"relation":"purpose","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":219,"left":208,"right":218,"relation":"explanation","nuclearity":"NS"}